NATIONAL flags will fly at half-mast in Free State when the late Free State Stars boss Mike Mokoena gets laid to rest in Bethlehem on Friday. President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared a special official category 2 funeral, following a request for a provincial send-off by the Free State Premier Sisi Ntombela in honour of Mokoena's role in the development of football in the province. The request has been approved on condition that the funeral service complies with the Covid-19 lockdown regulations.Ntombela has welcomed the president's decision, saying Mokoena has served football with the highest level of dedication and commitment. A special official provincial funeral category 2 entails elements of police ceremonial honours in line with Presidency's provincial funeral policy. The local football fraternity has been mourning since Mokoena passed away last week.